step.output:
📊 **Analysis Summary**:
- Total issues: {{issues_list.length}}
- Critical: {{issues_list.filter(i => i.severity == "CRITICAL").length}}
- Medium: {{issues_list.filter(i => i.severity == "MEDIUM").length}}
- Low: {{issues_list.filter(i => i.severity == "LOW").length}}

step.loop:

🔧 [{{loop.index}}/{{issues_list.length}}] Fixing: {{issue.description}}
   Section: {{issue.section}}
   Lines: {{issue.line_range}}
   Severity: {{issue.severity}}




          ⚠️ Large fix detected ({{issue.estimated_lines}} lines), splitting into chunks...
          Split fix content into chunks of {max_edit_size} lines
          Set {{chunks}} = split result


        <check if="{{issue.estimated_lines}} <= {max_edit_size}">
          Set {{chunks}} = [single fix content]



        Set {{chunk_success}} = true
        Set {{retry_count}} = 0




          Prepare Edit operation:
            - file_path: {story_dir}/{{story_key}}.md
            - search_start_line: {{chunk.start_line}}
            - search: {{chunk.original_content}}
            - replace: {{chunk.fixed_content}}



            Execute Edit tool with prepared parameters
               ✅ Chunk {{chunk.index}}/{{chunks.length}} applied



               ❌ Edit failed: {{error.message}}

            <check if="{{retry_count}} < 3">
              Increment {{retry_count}}



                   🔄 Reducing chunk size and retrying (attempt {{retry_count}}/3)...
                Reduce chunk size by 50%
                Re-split current chunk



              <check if="{{chunk.size}} <= 50">
                   🔄 Retrying with same parameters (attempt {{retry_count}}/3)...
                Wait 2 seconds





                 ⚠️ Max retries exceeded, skipping this fix
              Set {{chunk_success}} = false
              Add to {{failed_fixes}}: {{issue}}






          Increment {{fixed_count}}
             ✅ Fix applied successfully




          Reload story file to verify integrity

            ❌ **Error: File integrity check failed**

The file may have been corrupted during editing.

            Return FAILURE with error: "File integrity check failed after {{fixed_count}} fixes"

